background_story: Darius was known for his laid-back approach to parenting. He believed in giving his children the freedom to make their own choices, often to the point of permissiveness. His house was always filled with friends of his kids, and he rarely said no to their requests. While some might view his approach as lenient, Darius saw it as a way to foster independence and self-reliance in his children. However, as they grew older, his kids sometimes took advantage of his permissiveness, pushing boundaries and testing limits. Darius had to navigate the fine line between giving his children autonomy and teaching them responsibility, learning that sometimes, setting boundaries was necessary for their growth and well-being.
